<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1E1E1E><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/udohpazxorbelbeeb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dohpaz Xorbelbeeb</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 415<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/01 12:09:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclefrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yin and Yang</span><hr size=1> He stood there. <br>
<br>
The bodies were scattered everywhere. There wasn't any other word to describe it. It was carnage.<br>
<br>
In his rage he had become one with the magic and unleashed such a hellstorm that even the gods took notice of his actions.<br>
<br>
Scattered body parts that would've easily made him gag before were just another part of the scenery. He stood in the middle. He was the source of everything. He was the fury that had made the storm.<br>
<br>
He knew Soulshiver had much honor and would not turn against his own kind even though they had betrayed him to the highest degree.<br>
<br>
But the little magician called Dohpaz Xorbelbeeb was not as honorable, deep inside him he had the heart of a killer.<br>
<br>
He hadn't thought twice about it. He had avenged the death of his blood-brother Soulshiver.<br>
<br>
As the council lay there on the floor motionless, Dohpaz summoned back his elemental that was slaying everything in sight.<br>
<br>
He lifted his arms in the air and in one quick motion brought everything within 15 feet of him ablaze. <br>
<br>
He was the fire that burned, the fire that cleansed, he was the flame of vengeance.<br>
<br>
The council was dead, Neriak would return to anarchy as it was before. Blood Circle would no longer feel the pain that the council inflicted upon them.<br>
<br>
High atop their clouds, the Gods argued what to do with this little gnome that had channeled the power of the God's themselves. They were frightened of him.<br>
<br>
Innorukk stood up and shouted at the others.<br>
<br>
- &quot;It is time that we end his life. He will be a thorn in our side from this day forth until he is dead!!!&quot;<br>
<br>
The mother of all stood and calmly waved her hand.<br>
<br>
- &quot;There is another solution to our problem apart from killing this little one. We could always open a gateway to another world and let him choose wether to stay or go. If he stays you can have your way Innorukk, but it must be his choice, he must decide his fate without us intervening.&quot;<br>
<br>
All of the gods agreed and gathered together to cast the runes to open the portal...<br>
<br>
<br>
Dohpaz felt a magical force in front of him. He had never seen something as complex before and had never thought something like this could be done.<br>
<br>
Before him stood now a window. It wasn't a gate. A gate could only take you across this world. This was a window to another dimension. Having avenged his blood brother, Dohpaz would surely be hunted down by the followers of the council. He did not plan on hiding for the rest of his life.<br>
<br>
As he approached the window, he could hear a faint whisper. A voice filled with soothing melodies and that seemed to smell like honey.<br>
<br>
- &quot;You... have... chosen... wisely.... little one...&quot;<br>
<br>
Dohpaz smiled and stepped through.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Dohpaz Xorbelbeeb <br>
55 Conjurer<br>
Proud member of Blood Circle <p><div align=center>
